            <Title>anthologies force a tokenism approach to diversity</Title>
            <Text>‘Rethinking the canon’ means adding Charlotte Smith to William Wordsworth’s ‘contexts’, or [salaciously?] peering through the crossed-out lines of Dorothy Wordsworth’s journal, or giving a monumental number of pages to Mary Shelley: it’s looking at a man, finding the nearest woman, and shoving her in. This is better than NOT shoving them in — tokenism at least lets marginalized voices be heard! — But it doesn’t fundamentally the status quo. Distant reading can at least try to.</Text>
