            <Text>Vintage “small data”: playing with an Index to Tears
PUBLISHED ON September 29, 2017
I love indexes. They’re like spreadsheets in disguise, (and as previously established, I love spreadsheets). So when I was reading Henry Mackenzie’s Man of Feeling (1771) for my special fields exam, and I noticed that the Victorian edition digitized for Project Gutenbergincluded an “index to tears” for the novel… well, I got a little carried away.
The index itself provides the page numbers on which characters cry, and a brief extract from the novel’s description:
